U.S. Stocks Gain on Report G-20 Weighing $600 Billion IMF Lending Program

-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 
2011-12-07T20:44:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-07/u-s-stocks-gain-on-report-g-20-weighing-600-billion-imf-lending-program.html
U.S. stocks extended gains after
Nikkei reported that the Group of 20 nations is considering a
$600 billion  International Monetary Fund  lending program to halt
 Europe ’s debt crisis.  The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index climbed 0.5 percent to
1,264.70 at 3:43 p.m. in  New York .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael P. Regan at 
 mregan12@bloomberg.net  